name: Beanie Weenie Quesadilla Rolls
author: Bella
summary: This treat was born out of ready-to-be-used leftovers and my desire to create something new and fun for our 6-year-old to have for lunch.  This is now one of his favorites (Grampa's too!).
ingredients: ¼ cup condensed bean with bacon soup
directions: Pour soup into a small microwave safe bowl
Wrap tortilla and hot dog with a clean, lightly moist cloth
Place soup, tortilla, and hot dog in microwave and cook on high approximately 30 seconds, or until tortilla is hot and pliable and the soup is hot
Place hot dog and soup in center of tortilla; sprinkle with cheese and roll
Microwave for an additional 10 seconds to fully melt the cheese
